Implemented the SQLAlchemy 2 modernization inside the allowed surface only. Repository reads now use `select(...)` and no longer own commits in [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run3/workspace/app/repository.py:1). The API create path now stays inside the caller’s transaction instead of committing from the repository layer in [app/api.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run3/workspace/app/api.py:1).

The worker and admin CLI now each own an explicit begin/commit/rollback unit of work, so forced failures roll back `processing`/`queued` state instead of leaking retry state across attempts: [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run3/workspace/app/worker.py:1), [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run3/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:1). I also rewrote the deploy note to reflect the prior rollback, required recovery checks, and precise rollback steps in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run3/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1).

Validation passed with the exact required command: `pytest -q tests/test_api.py tests/test_worker.py tests/test_admin_cli.py` -> `3 passed`. The only warning was pytest being unable to write `.pytest_cache` outside the writable area.
